 ('1182', '1002', 'en_us', 'Search Permits by Business Types', '', '<p>CalGold is a state-operated website that provides a list of the regional, state, and federal licenses and permits required for businesses in each California city.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-27 23:04:31', '2016-03-03 02:12:28', '7133f78e-b4fa-4d5f-8a3a-e03d1491d660'),
 ('1192', '1012', 'en_us', 'Common Permit Types', 'Learn more about permits that are required by common business types', '<p>The following are standard permits required for common types of businesses. However, this is not a complete list for all types of businesses.&nbsp; Make sure to check CalGold website to get the permits needed for your type of business, as described at the bottom of this page.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>City of Oakland Requirements</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Building Permits</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Building permits are documents which are obtained through the Office of Planning and Building authorizing the start of construction or remodeling of a building in the City of Oakland. There are four types of permits which may be required:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ol><li>Building</li><li>Electrical</li><li>Plumbing</li><li>Mechanical</li></ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.oaklandnet.com/government/ceda/revised/building_permits.html\">Get more details from Building Services</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Rent Adjustment</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you rent out one or more residential units, you may be subject to the City of Oakland’s Rent Program service fee of $30 per year per unit.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://cedaonline.oaklandnet.com/rentadjustmentsite/index.htm\">Get details here</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Excess Litter Fee</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you are operating one of the types of businesses below, you may be subject to the Excess Litter Fee.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Fast food restaurants\r\n\r\n</li><li>Convenience markets\r\n\r\n</li><li>Gasoline station markets\r\n\r\n</li><li>Liquor stores&nbsp;</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.oaklandnet.com/documents/WEBPAGEELF92206.pdf\">Get more details in this PDF file</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Peddler/Solicitor Permit</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you intend to sell or solicit door-to-door, you must obtain a peddler permit.&nbsp; Obtain the permit application at:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Oakland Police Department<br>455 7th Street, Room 306<br>Oakland, 94607.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Bring the completed Peddler Permit to the Business Tax office.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Fire Department Permits</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you are starting a new business, or are expanding an existing business in Oakland which includes the operation, and/or storage and/or manufacturing of a wide variety of items, you are required to submit a permit application to the Fire Prevention Office. Your application will be reviewed, an inspection of your business will be conducted, and a determination will be made as to the issuance of the permit.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Important note: Business owners are advised to&nbsp;</strong><strong>meet with the Oakland Fire Department early on</strong>&nbsp;in your planning stage, as many permits are rejected annually due to wrong use code and other issues found during the inspection phase. Meeting with the Oakland Fire Department from the onset will save you time and money as you are starting or expanding your business. Don\'t assume that your business doesn\'t apply!</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.oaklandnet.com/fire/fpb/\">Get more details from the Fire Prevention Office</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>County and State&nbsp;Requirements</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Fictitious Business Name</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>You must register your business name with the Alameda County Clerk-Recorder\'s Office.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.acgov.org/auditor/clerk/filefbn1.htm\">More details from Alameda County Clerk-Recorder\'s Office</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Retail/Wholesale Sales</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you will be selling retail or wholesale items which require collection of state sales taxes, you need a Sellers Permit.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.boe.ca.gov/\">More details from California State Board of Equalization</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Food Establishments</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you will be serving and selling food, you must obtain a health permit before applying for your Business Tax Certificate.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.acgov.org/aceh/\">More details from Alameda County Environmental Health</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Alcoholic Beverage Sales</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you intend to sell alcoholic beverages, you must have an Alcoholic Beverage License.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.abc.ca.gov/\">More details from California state Alcoholic Beverage Control</a></p><h3>Hazardous Waste</h3><p>If your company intends to deal with hazardous waste&nbsp;(such as solvents, motor oil, paints, pesticides, fertilizers,&nbsp;aerosol, etc), you will need to apply for a hazardous waste permit with the County of Alameda.</p><p>For more details, call&nbsp;Alameda County Environmental Health at 1&nbsp;(510) 567-6702 or visit their <a href=\"https://www.acgov.org/aceh/\">website</a>.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-27 23:10:58', '2016-03-03 02:12:28', '17d7a837-50a3-4e95-a324-2299c5c2291d'),
 ('1202', '1022', 'en_us', 'Recruit and Train Employees', '', '<p>There are several organizations, government agencies, and online materials to help you find, hire, and manage employees.&nbsp;&nbsp;Check out the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://oaklandbusinesscenter.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=47&Itemid=53\">Employees&nbsp;</a>section of this site for more information.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-27 23:17:26', '2016-03-03 02:12:29', 'c572876f-a897-4ad6-bf2b-fe630742838e'),
 ('1212', '1032', 'en_us', 'Green your Business', 'Local resources to help businesses learn how to go green, get certified, and network with other green businesses.', '<h2>Getting Certified</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Alameda County Green Business Program</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Alameda County Green Business Program offers certification for&nbsp; businesses that can demonstrate that they practice resource conservation (water and energy) and pollution prevention (toxics reduction). In addition to recognizing businesses for their green practices, Certified Green Businesses can use the highly recognizable logo on their advertising and are able to network with other Green Businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.greenbiz.ca.gov/AboutUsAC.html\">Green Business Information & Application</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Green America (formerly Co-Op America)</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Green America’s mission is to harness economic power&mdash;the strength of consumers, businesses and the marketplace&mdash;to create a socially just and environmentally sustainable society. Green America helps consumers find socially- and environmentally-responsible businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.greenamericatoday.org/cabn/join/index.cfm\">Click here to learn more and join Green America.</a><br>&nbsp;<br></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Resources for Greening Your Business</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Business Recycling and Waste Reduction in Oakland</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Check the StopWaste.org website for comprehensive information on recycling, composting, reuse, and waste reduction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://stopwaste.org/\">StopWaste.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>East Bay Energy Watch</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>PG&E, the cities of Oakland and Berkeley, the counties of Alameda and Contra Costa are working together on the East Bay Energy Watch (EBEW). BEW promotes reduced energy use and energy savings targets by providing energy efficiency information and direct installation of energy efficient&nbsp;equipment to eligible PG&E customers including lighting, refrigeration, building heating and cooling and other energy systems used by businesses.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.pge.com/ebep\">www.pge.com/ebep</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>City of Oakland Green Business Projects</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The City has a department dedicated to green business projects and resources.&nbsp; For the latest resources, contact the Business Assistance Center.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Classes</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://oaklandbusinesscenter.com/index.php?option=com_mtree&task=advsearch2&search_id=61&Itemid=82\">See a list of organizations that provide green business classes&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Promoting and Networking with Other Green Businesses</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.sustainablebiz.org/\">Sustainable Business Alliance</a>&nbsp;<br>Based in Berkeley, the Sustainable Business Alliance is a membership organization for Bay Area companies committed to greater environmental and socially responsible business practices.&nbsp; Workshops and networking events every month!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://greenchamberofcommerce.net/\">Green Chamber of Commerce</a>&nbsp;<br>The Green Chamber of Commerce is dedicated to fostering the success of businesses committed to environmental and social responsibility. Based in the Bay Area, the Green Chamber is working to build chapters across the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.greenbiz.ca.gov/ShopGreen.html\">Certified Green Businesses</a><br>As mentioned above, Alameda County certifies green businesses.&nbsp; When you become certified, you join a network of other green businesses, and will be invited to green businesses events.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table><tbody><tr>\r\n</tr></tbody></table>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-01-29 23:26:05', '2016-03-03 02:12:29', '9c07485a-9928-4b85-879c-652272e7b1fd'),
 ('1222', '1042', 'en_us', 'Connect with Local Business Communities and Advisors', 'Local organizations to join to grow your network and get advice for your business', '<p>Businesses of all stages and sizes can benefit from advisors and programs to help them build smart strategies for long term survival and growth. Here are some resources to help you out.</p><h4>Sustainable Business Alliance</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://sustainablebusinessalliance.org\">Sustainable Business Alliance</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>A business association committed to building a vibrant community of locally-owned, sustainably-minded businesses in the East Bay.&nbsp;<br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Providing our members with opportunities for networking, business development, and learning best practices for operating sustainably.</li><li>Educating the public on the benefits of local living economies and encouraging residents and businesses to spend locally.</li><li>Supporting public policy changes that advance sustainable economic development, through our affiliation with the American Sustainable Business Council.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Oakland Grown</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.oaklandgrown.org/\">www.oaklandgrown.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Our vision includes the creation of a permanent local network that:<br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Supports the growth and development of locally owned and independently operated businesses and local artists in Oakland</li><li>Encourages local purchasing by residents, businesses, and artists</li><li>Creates opportunities for business owners and artists to network and share best practices</li><li>Advocates for public policies that strengthen independent local businesses and artists, and helps level the economic playing field.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Alameda County Small Business Development Center</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://oaklandbusinesscenter.com/index.php?option=com_mtree&task=visit&link_id=9&Itemid=82\">www.acsbdc.org</a><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Expert consulting, top-notch seminars, linkages to other resource providers and business planning services to business owners interested in accelerating the success of their ventures.</li><li>Consulting is free, and most workshops are also free.&nbsp;Our team of Business Advisors come from a variety of high-growth industries and corporate backgrounds and work hands-on with clients to address challenges and seize opportunities.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Business Value Alliance</h4>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>www.<a href=\"http://oaklandbusinesscenter.com/index.php?option=com_mtree&task=visit&link_id=42&Itemid=82\">businessvaluealliance.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>BVA equips motivated owners with practical methods, tools and strategic business tools to improve business performance and grow for the long-term.&nbsp;</li><li>BVA offers several programs and services, including: a variety of workshops, a 9-month group program called Created in Oakland, a Business Growth Design Studio, and custom one-on-one advising on business growth.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Inner City Advisors</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.innercityadvisors.org\">www.innercityadvisors.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Inner City Advisors (ICA) helps build sustainable and responsible inner city businesses that create quality jobs, reinvest in the community and contribute to the local economy. We accomplish our mission by providing our Portfolio Companies and other local entrepreneurs with&nbsp;high caliber consulting, strategic advice, entrepreneurship education and access to resources and professional networks.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Renaissance Entrepreneurship Center</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.rencenter.org\">www.rencenter.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The mission of Renaissance Entrepreneurship Center is to empower and increase the entrepreneurial capacities of socially and economically diverse women and men, and thereby strengthen our communities through the creation of sustainable new businesses, new jobs, and the promotion of financial self-sufficiency.<br></p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Urban FIRE</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.urbanfire.org\">www.urbanfire.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Urban FIRE (Financial Intelligence, Responsible Entrepreneurship) is training to start and sustain a micro-business based on a proven, real world experiential system. Ignite your passion, burn the status quo and light a path to self determination. Our brand of entrepreneurship is about your personal success, business as a \"B Corp\"(<a href=\"http://www.bcorporation.net),social\">www.bcorporation.net)</a>, social&nbsp;justice and building our local economy - because we all live in an intradependent urban society. Urban FIRE meets weekly for three hours for 24 weeks divided into two semesters. There is no greater purpose than launching the genius that lies within you and creating a rewarding business that speaks to your soul. Urban FIRE Entrepreneurship is more than just about business, it\'s about building a successful life. We partner with Oakland Adult and Career Education to offer our classes at a price affordable to everyone.<br></p>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<p>For an advanced search of additional organizations click <a href=\"http://oaklandbusinesscenter.com/index.php?option=com_mtree&task=advsearch\">here.</a>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-01 22:13:38', '2016-03-03 02:12:29', '31f16c1a-a93d-4c23-9e50-e33c648cda08'),
 ('1232', '1052', 'en_us', 'Get Consultation on What Permits You Will Need', '', '<p>Figuring out what permits you may need for your business can be a complicated process. We recommend talking to a business permitting specialist either in person or on the phone. Some permits can be easily approved over the counter&nbsp;while others may take additional time based on factors such as exterior&nbsp;designs, late night hours, or parking.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Visit or Call Us</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Oakland Business Assistance Center<br>270 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza<br>1&nbsp;(510)&nbsp;238-7952<br>Monday – Friday&nbsp;<br>9:00 a.m. – 5:00 p.m.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Talk with a Specialist</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Keira Williams<br></strong><em>Retail</em><br>(510) 238-3853<br><a href=\"mailto:kwilliams@oaklandnet.com\">kwilliams@oaklandnet.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Marisa Raya</strong><br><em>Technology</em><br>(510) 238-6230&nbsp;<br><a href=\"mailto:mraya@oaklandnet.com\">mraya@oaklandnet.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steve Lautze</strong><br><em>Green, Recycle-based, or Alternative Energy</em><br>(510) 238-4973<br><a href=\"mailto:slautze@oaklandnet.com\">slautze@oaklandnet.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Margot Lederer Prado</strong><br><em>Manufacturing and Industrial Uses, Arts/Engineering/Design, Food and Beverage, Healthcare and Wellness</em><br>(510) 238-6766 &nbsp;&nbsp;<br><a href=\"mailto:mprado@oaklandnet.com\">mprado@oaklandnet.com</a></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-04 00:09:53', '2016-03-03 02:12:30', '08275529-138c-47a6-bfe7-7a367aa8910f'),
