 ('4372', '392', 'es', 'Requesting a Civil Service Board Hearing or Appeal', '', '<h3 id=\"what-to-know\">What to Know</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a <strong>permanent classified employee</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>You can appeal the following disciplinary actions:</li>\r\n  <li>Suspension</li>\r\n  <li>Fine</li>\r\n  <li>Demotion</li>\r\n  <li>Discharge</li>\r\n  <li>The Personnel Director receives all notices of appeal.</li>\r\n  <li>Submit your notice of appeal within 10 working days of the final notice of discipline.</li>\r\n  <li>Your union has defined rules to file an appeal and request a hearing in a Memorandum of Understanding.</li>\r\n  <li>Click here to find your union’s Memorandum of Understanding (MOUs) http://www2.oaklandnet.com/Government/o/CityAdministration/d/EmployeeRelations/MOUsandCivilServiceRules/index.htm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a <strong>probationary classified employee</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>You can appeal losing your job under certain conditions.</li>\r\n  <li>If you were not evaluated according to the rules of the Personnel Manual.</li>\r\n  <li>If you were not released according to the rules of the Personnel Manual.</li>\r\n  <li>The Personnel Director receives all notices of appeal.</li>\r\n  <li>Submit your notice of appeal within 5 working days of notice of losing your job.</li>\r\n  <li>Your union has defined rules to file an appeal and request a hearing in a Memorandum of Understanding.</li>\r\n  <li>Click here to find your union’s Memorandum of Understanding (MOUs) http://www2.oaklandnet.com/Government/o/CityAdministration/d/EmployeeRelations/MOUsandCivilServiceRules/index.htm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"what-happens-next\">What Happens Next</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>You will receive a response to your notice of appeal within 7 days.</li>\r\n  <li>Timely appeals must be submitted to the Civil Service Board.</li>\r\n  <li>The Board will decide who will hear the appeal.</li>\r\n  <li>Either the Board or an independent Hearing Officer will hear the appeal.</li>\r\n  <li>Hearings are usually closed to the public unless you request a public hearing.</li>\r\n  <li>The Board has the power to make a final decision.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"contact-the-civil-service-board\">Contact the Civil Service Board</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr><th>In Person</th><th>Phone</th><th>Email</th></tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:white\">\r\nHours: Monday through Friday from 8:30 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.\r\n</td><td>\r\nGeneral Information: (510) 238-6467\r\n\r\nAppeals: (510) 238-6467</td>\r\n<td>\r\n[civilservice@oaklandnet.com](mailto://civilservice@oaklandnet.com)\r\n</td> </tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"more-resources\">More Resources</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Ordinances 8979, 11777, the Personnel Manual - Civil Service Board and the Personnel Rules and Procedures of the Port of Oakland (Appellate duties of the Civil Service Board)</li>\r\n  <li>Rule 10 of the Personnel Manual (Permanent Classified Employee Rights for Appeal to the Civil Service Board)</li>\r\n  <li>Rule 6 of the Personnel Manual (Probationary Classified Employee Rights for Appeal to the Civil Service Board)</li>\r\n  <li>Protocol for Hearing Packet Submission http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/hrm/documents/form/oak052475.pdf</li>\r\n  <li>Hearing Request Form http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/hrm/documents/form/oak052473.pdf</li>\r\n  <li>Rule 6 Probationary Period Procedure in Appeals (PDF) http://www.oaklandnet.com/Civil%20Service/Rule6.pdf</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL