 ('6612', '3212', 'en_us', 'Challenge a Rent Increase (Draft)', '', '<h3>Understanding Legal&nbsp;Rent Increases</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Increases are limited to the CPI adjustment announced each year by the Residential Rent Adjustment Program unless the landlord can justify a higher amount. The law limits these to specific reasons for a higher rent increase.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Only one increase is allowed in a twelve month period.</li><li>Rent can be increased&nbsp;if their are improvements or major repairs that add value to the property.</li><li>Rent can be increased if there has been an increase in housing service costs such as taxes, insurance, utilities, water, garbage, mantainence, or managerial costs.</li><li>In some cases, rent can be increased if there is an increase in debt service cost.</li><li>Rent can be increased due to a previous deferred annual adjustment.</li><li>Generally, if tenants do not file a petition within 60 days of receiving a rent increase, they will lose their rights to challenge the increase.</li><li>In most cases, there is no limit on increases when a tenant moves out and a new tenant moves in. Once the new tenant moves in, future increases are limited by the Rent Law.</li></ul><p><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/ceda/documents/form/dowd008123.pdf\">Read the Full Letter for Tenants About Rent Increase Policies</a></p><p><br></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Understand the Process of Challenging a Rent Increase</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol><li>File a Petition with the Rent Adjustment Board.</li><li><strong>Optional:</strong>&nbsp;Attend a mediation session with your landlord to see if you can reach an agreement.</li><li>Schedule a hearing with the Rent Adjustment Board.</li><li>Prepare evidence and witnesses for the hearing.</li><li>Go to your hearing.</li></ol>\r\n\r\n<p>The Hearing Officer will decide what to do about the increase based on their interpretation of the law. You and your landlord must obey the decision.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/ceda/documents/form/dowd008122.pdf\">Read the Full Tenants Guide for Detailed Information</a></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'hide', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-03-30 20:53:06', '2016-04-07 23:00:18', '745afaf6-4d85-42c9-a28d-3755b37939db'),
