 ('26', '11', '2', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Free Parking on Plaid Friday & Saturdays until New Year\'s\",\"slug\":\"free-parking-on-plaid-friday-saturdays-until-new-years\",\"postDate\":1449775614,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>As part of the Shop Oakland Grown for the Holidays campaign, the City of Oakland will offer&nbsp;free parking every Saturday until New Year\'s Day plus Plaid Friday (November 27).&nbsp;The free parking applies to on-street meters (both individual meters and multi-space kiosks), four City-owned parking lots and four City-owned parking garages. Posted time limits&nbsp;at meters&nbsp;still apply.<\\/p>\",\"2\":\"\"}}', '2015-12-10 19:26:54', '2015-12-10 19:26:54', 'accd9455-2cf8-4165-a099-5f1b4f3f659e'),
 ('27', '12', '2', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Oakland\\u2019s Minimum Wage Goes Up January 1, Deadline for noticing requirement is December 15\",\"slug\":\"oaklands-minimum-wage-goes-up-january-1-deadline-for-noticing-requirement-is-december-15\",\"postDate\":1449776225,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Oakland\\u2019s Measure FF, a voter-enacted ballot measure passed in November 2014, provides annual increases to Oakland\\u2019s Minimum Wage based on the local Consumer Price Index (CPI). Effective January 1, 2016, the rate rises 30\\u00a2, from $12.25 to $12.55. The law requires that employers inform employees of the increase by December 15, 2015.<\\/p>\",\"2\":\"\"}}', '2015-12-10 19:37:05', '2015-12-10 19:37:05', '061ab6bd-a834-4421-9319-86f824065bc5'),
