 ('2352', '1072', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Lauching and Marketing Your Business\",\"slug\":\"lauching-and-marketing-your-business\",\"postDate\":1454715276,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>There are a variety of marketing services and opportunities available to Oakland businesses.<\\/p><h3>Get Grand Opening Assistance<\\/h3><p>The City of Oakland\'s Marketing department helps new businesses with press releases and events to announce their new businesses.&nbsp; Contact the Public Information Officer at 1&nbsp;(510)&nbsp;238-2107.<\\/p><h3>Oakland Grown<\\/h3><p>The Oakland Grown campaign is Oakland\\u2019s campaign to encourage people to support locally-owned businesses and artists when they shop.&nbsp; Oakland businesses and artists that are locally-based and independently owned can get decals, listings on the Shop Oakland Grown website and other marketing benefits.&nbsp; Learn more on the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/oaklandgrown.org\\/join.php\\\">Oakland Grown website<\\/a>.<\\/p><h3>Marketing Green Businesses<\\/h3><p><font face=\\\"sans-serif\\\"><\\/font>Certified Green Businesses take advantage of the decals, website listings and other marketing that the Alameda County Green Business program does to promote green businesses. To become a green business and benefit from these marketing benefits, check out the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.greenbiz.ca.gov\\/ShopGreenAC.html#legal\\\">Alameda County Green Business website<\\/a>. &nbsp; &nbsp;<\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\",\"5\":\"\",\"92\":\"\",\"3\":\"\",\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-05 23:34:36', '2016-02-05 23:34:36', 'd02492dc-cf25-4774-a647-dfe3c9c58ff2'),
 ('2362', '1072', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Lauching and Marketing Your Business\",\"slug\":\"lauching-and-marketing-your-business\",\"postDate\":1454715240,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"742\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>There are a variety of marketing services and opportunities available to Oakland businesses.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Get Grand Opening Assistance<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The City of Oakland\'s Marketing department helps new businesses with press releases and events to announce their new businesses.&nbsp; Contact the Public Information Officer at 1&nbsp;(510)&nbsp;238-2107.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Oakland Grown<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Oakland Grown campaign is Oakland\\u2019s campaign to encourage people to support locally-owned businesses and artists when they shop.&nbsp; Oakland businesses and artists that are locally-based and independently owned can get decals, listings on the Shop Oakland Grown website and other marketing benefits.&nbsp; Learn more on the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/oaklandgrown.org\\/join.php\\\">Oakland Grown website<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Marketing Green Businesses<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Certified Green Businesses take advantage of the decals, website listings and other marketing that the Alameda County Green Business program does to promote green businesses. To become a green business and benefit from these marketing benefits, check out the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.greenbiz.ca.gov\\/ShopGreenAC.html#legal\\\">Alameda County Green Business website<\\/a>. &nbsp; &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\",\"5\":\"\",\"92\":\"\",\"3\":\"\",\"4\":\"The City provides a variety of services to help you market your business\"}}', '2016-02-05 23:50:00', '2016-02-05 23:50:00', '5ff32dbe-b081-4823-82aa-869da73f249a'),
 ('2372', '982', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Get your Business Inspections\",\"slug\":\"get-your-business-inspections\",\"postDate\":1453935180,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"1062\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Certain types of businesses may require inspections by the Health Department, Police Department, or Fire Prevention & Inspection Department.&nbsp;This step can be complex and we recommend you&nbsp;contact the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/oaklandbusinesscenter.com\\/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=102&Itemid=85\\\">Business Assistance Center<\\/a>&nbsp;to&nbsp;determine what inspections you will need.<\\/p><p>Schedule an Building Inspection<\\/p><p>Schedule a Health Inspection<\\/p><p>Schedule a Fire Prevention Inspection<\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\",\"5\":\"\",\"92\":\"\",\"3\":\"\",\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-06 02:21:34', '2016-02-06 02:21:34', '52981402-65b8-46da-8338-b0aa36c2b4c6'),
 ('2382', '952', '3', '442', 'en_us', '5', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Obtain Your Business License\",\"slug\":\"obtain-your-business-license\",\"postDate\":1453934640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"922\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h3>Cost<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The $60 registration fee must be paid and filed within 30 days of starting your business.&nbsp; If you file your registration later than 30 days after you start your business, you will need to pay a small penalty plus interest for each month beyond the 30 days.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Application Process<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The application is available at the office or as a&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.oaklandnet.com\\/government\\/fwawebsite\\/revenue\\/revenue_newbiaapp.htm\\\">PDF online<\\/a>. You can pay by cash, check or credit card. The application can&nbsp;be returned by fax (with a&nbsp;credit card), via mail or in person.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 1320<br>Oakland, CA 94612<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Time frame<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You will get a paper certificate from the business tax office approximately two weeks after you pay your fee.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>More Info<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Get the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.oaklandnet.com\\/government\\/fwawebsite\\/revenue\\/revenue_biztax.htm\\\">business application (PDF), business tax classification and rate table, additional&nbsp;information, and FAQs<\\/a>&nbsp;on the City\'s Finance and Management Agency website.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Businesses located in or operating in Oakland need to pay an annual business tax on or before March 1 of each year.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/oaklandbusinesscenter.com\\/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=37&Itemid=50\\\">See more details on the annual business tax here.<\\/a><br>&nbsp;<br><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/oaklandbusinesscenter.com\\/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=102&Itemid=85\\\">Visit the BAC or request help from the BAC online<\\/a>&nbsp;if you have additional questions or need more information.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><\\/tr><\\/tbody><\\/table>\",\"5\":\"http:\\/\\/www.oaklandnet.com\\/government\\/fwawebsite\\/revenue\\/revenue_newbiaapp.htm\",\"92\":\"\",\"3\":\"Download the application form\",\"4\":\"To conduct any business in Oakland you must first obtain a Business License, known as a Business Tax Certificate, and pay an annual business tax.\"}}', '2016-02-08 17:58:23', '2016-02-08 17:58:23', '93b5f17f-8547-48be-891a-fd6cf2fa3be5'),
