 ('3442', '862', '3', '1', 'en_us', '4', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Choose a Suitable Location\",\"slug\":\"find-a-location\",\"postDate\":1453930440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"912\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h3>Some Factors to Consider<\\/h3><ol><li>What kind of location best suites your target customers (who walks by and who comes to visit the neighborhood)?&nbsp;<\\/li><li>How much space do you need?<\\/li><li>What kind of space will you need?<\\/li><li>What are the lease terms?<\\/li><li>What can you afford to pay?<\\/li><li>How much parking do you need?<\\/li><\\/ol><p>There are several resources to help you find a business location in Oakland, including city staff, commercial brokers, website listings, and shopping district leaders.&nbsp;The City of Oakland Business Assistance Center can provide market analysis on neighborhood profiles, demographic reports, and more.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"\",\"linkTitle\":\"Request Assistance from the BAC\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/oaklandbusinesscenter.com\\/request.html\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 23:12:42', '2016-02-10 23:12:42', '5b695e20-6688-4c92-ad1f-f12bdb7557f5'),
 ('3452', '932', '3', '1', 'en_us', '4', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Start Your Utilities\",\"slug\":\"start-your-utilities\",\"postDate\":1453933500,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"1362\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>PG&E (Pacific Gas and Electric) is the local utility company. Make sure to contact PG&E as soon as you find your location to get all of your utilities in order.&nbsp; Depending on the services you need, you may need to wait for assistance.&nbsp;It is recommended that you get your requests in early.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1592\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"\",\"linkTitle\":\"Visit PG&E Online\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/pge.com\\/\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 23:13:02', '2016-02-10 23:13:02', '46a755c2-d41d-4f86-9a31-fe409583ca71'),
 ('3462', '1712', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Check Zoning Regulations for Your Property\",\"slug\":\"check-zoning-regulations-for-your-property\",\"postDate\":1455146408,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"912\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Once you have a couple of location options, you should check&nbsp;the planning map and zoning code&nbsp;to see if your location outright permitted, conditionally permitted or not permitted.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>This step can be complicated depending on the type of business. Unless you are familiar with planning and zoning regulations, we recommend you talk with a planner at the City of&nbsp;Oakland.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"new4\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"Talk to a Planner\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Permit Center<br><\\/strong>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 2114<br>Oakland, CA 94612<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Online Resource\",\"linkTitle\":\"See the Zoning Map\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/mapgis.oaklandnet.com\\/planmap\\/\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Online Resource\",\"linkTitle\":\"Read the Planning Code\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/report\\/oak053289.pdf\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 23:20:08', '2016-02-10 23:20:08', '7151a042-13e5-4b64-93a3-05c49ea62918'),
 ('3472', '862', '3', '1', 'en_us', '5', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Choose a Suitable Location\",\"slug\":\"find-a-location\",\"postDate\":1453930440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"912\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h3>Some Factors to Consider<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol><li>What kind of location best suites your target customers (who walks by and who comes to visit the neighborhood)?&nbsp;<\\/li><li>How much space do you need?<\\/li><li>What kind of space will you need?<\\/li><li>What are the lease terms?<\\/li><li>What can you afford to pay?<\\/li><li>How much parking do you need?<\\/li><\\/ol><p>We recommend that you have a strong&nbsp;understanding of&nbsp;the business, zoning\\/planning, and building permitting needs of your location before you sign your lease.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>There are several resources to help you find a business location in Oakland, including city staff, commercial brokers, website listings, and shopping district leaders.&nbsp;The City of Oakland Business Assistance Center can provide market analysis on neighborhood profiles, demographic reports, and more.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1702\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"\",\"linkTitle\":\"Request Assistance from the BAC\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/oaklandbusinesscenter.com\\/request.html\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-10 23:25:51', '2016-02-10 23:25:51', '180a55d6-1efe-483a-a8f2-b09e2711ece9'),
