 ('3612', '982', '3', '1', 'en_us', '14', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Schedule Your Building Inspections\",\"slug\":\"get-your-business-inspections\",\"postDate\":1453935180,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"1832\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h3>Building Services Hours<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Hours: Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, Friday 8:00a.m.- 4:00p.m&nbsp;and&nbsp;Wednesday 9:30a.m. - 4:00p.m.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Building Services inspections include mechanical, electrical, and plumbing inspections.<\\/p><p>Inspections are required to insure that the construction is proceeding according to the approved plans and project conditions-of-approval, and that all current code standards are being met. This will help to insure personal safety and to secure the value of the improvement.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It is your responsibility to schedule all inspections.&nbsp;An appointment must be made at least one working day in advance, and during busy construction months they may take several days to schedule.&nbsp;Periodic inspections must be scheduled until the project is completed and the City gives final approval.&nbsp;After the job has received a final inspection, the building permit will be kept on file in the Building Services Department as proof of the work completed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>During the construction phase, inspections by City Inspectors are required prior to:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Placing concrete or grout;<\\/li><li>Covering electrical, plumbing, or mechanical work;<\\/li><li>Covering floor framing;<\\/li><li>Covering interior sides of wall framing;<\\/li><li>Taping gypsum wallboard;<\\/li><li>Applying stucco;<\\/li><li>Insulation;<\\/li><li>Shower Walls prior to tiling;<\\/li><li>Exterior & Interior shear nailing;<\\/li><li>Waterproof membrane at exterior balconies, stairs etc;<\\/li><li>Roof plywood nailing;<\\/li><li>Roof framing;<\\/li><li>Shafts;<\\/li><li>Fire protection<\\/li><\\/ul><br><br><br><br><strong>Inspections are also required prior to connecting to, or the hook-up of:<\\/strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Gas lines;<\\/li><li>Electrical service; and\\/or<\\/li><li>Water and sewer services.<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>For more information, contact the Building Services Department at (510) 238-3444.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1762\":{\"type\":\"phoneNumber\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"phoneNumberTitle\":\"By Phone\",\"number\":\"1 (510) 238-3444 \",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"1772\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"In Person\",\"address\":\"<p>250 Frank Ogawa Plaza, 2nd Floor<br>Oakland, CA 94612<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-11 20:21:24', '2016-02-11 20:21:24', '2d7450f5-ac9e-491d-803b-d331df7cadf0'),
