 ('3652', '1092', '3', '1', 'en_us', '4', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Submit for Plan Check Review\",\"slug\":\"check-your-building-plan\",\"postDate\":1454962860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"1062\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Once you have submitted all of your&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/Government\\/o\\/PBN\\/OurServices\\/permits\\/index.htm\\\">required documents and building permit fees<\\/a>, our Building Services engineers will review your plans for&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/Government\\/o\\/PBN\\/OurOrganization\\/BuildingServices\\/s\\/codes\\/index.htm\\\">compliance with applicable codes and regulations<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Plan check for new dwellings usually takes four to six weeks. However, plans with special engineering may take longer. Building Services will also submit your plans to the Fire Services agency for review. Fire review takes 1-10&nbsp;days.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you apply for your&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/Government\\/o\\/PBN\\/OurServices\\/permits\\/index.htm\\\">Building Permit<\\/a>, Zoning staff will review the plans submitted to ensure that all conditions of approval are satisfied and that the plans are consistent with Zoning approval.&nbsp;If we return your plans to you for revision and resubmittal, plan check time will increase accordingly. For answers to your plan check questions, please call (510) 238-3891.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1582\":{\"type\":\"phoneNumber\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"phoneNumberTitle\":\"Call Us for Assistance\",\"number\":\"1 (510) 238-3891\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-16 22:47:44', '2016-02-16 22:47:44', 'b1d2dd45-70ff-49eb-88a6-f15e9e2f5017'),
 ('3662', '1802', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Schedule Your Inspections with Public Works\",\"slug\":\"schedule-your-inspections-with-public-works\",\"postDate\":1455221220,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"1832\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Public works issues permits regarding construction around the area of your property including:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol><li>CGS&nbsp;(curb, gutter, sidewalk, encroachment)<\\/li><li>X (excavations)<\\/li><li>SL (Sewer Lateral)<\\/li><li>P-Job (Infrastructure for larger projects around landscaping)<\\/li><\\/ol><p><br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>During stages of construction, you will need to schedule inspections with the Public Works department to make sure your space complies with these permits.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Public Works Department Hours<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Monday through Friday, 8:00AM to 5:00PM<br><\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1812\":{\"type\":\"phoneNumber\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"phoneNumberTitle\":\"By Phone\",\"number\":\"1 (510) 238-3961\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"1822\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"In Person\",\"address\":\"<p>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 4314\\u2028<br>Oakland, CA 94612<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-16 22:56:12', '2016-02-16 22:56:12', 'c4b42948-fd95-4b13-b92a-c8c9744ad520'),
 ('3672', '1052', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Get Consultation on What Permits You Will Need\",\"slug\":\"get-consultation-on-what-permits-you-will-need\",\"postDate\":1454544540,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"992\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Figuring out what permits you may need for your business can be a complicated process. We recommend talking to a business permitting specialist either in person or on the phone. Some permits can be easily approved over the counter&nbsp;while others may take additional time based on factors such as exterior&nbsp;designs, late night hours, or parking.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Visit or Call Us<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Oakland Business Assistance Center<br>270 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza<br>1&nbsp;(510)&nbsp;238-7952<br>Monday \\u2013 Friday&nbsp;<br>9:00 a.m. \\u2013 5:00 p.m.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Talk with a Specialist<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Keira Williams<br><\\/strong><em>Retail<\\/em><br>(510) 238-3853<br><a href=\\\"mailto:kwilliams@oaklandnet.com\\\">kwilliams@oaklandnet.com<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Marisa Raya<\\/strong><br><em>Technology<\\/em><br>(510) 238-6230&nbsp;<br><a href=\\\"mailto:mraya@oaklandnet.com\\\">mraya@oaklandnet.com<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Steve Lautze<\\/strong><br><em>Green, Recycle-based, or Alternative Energy<\\/em><br>(510) 238-4973<br><a href=\\\"mailto:slautze@oaklandnet.com\\\">slautze@oaklandnet.com<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Margot Lederer Prado<\\/strong><br><em>Manufacturing and Industrial Uses, Arts\\/Engineering\\/Design, Food and Beverage, Healthcare and Wellness<\\/em><br>(510) 238-6766 &nbsp;&nbsp;<br><a href=\\\"mailto:mprado@oaklandnet.com\\\">mprado@oaklandnet.com<\\/a><\\/p>\",\"312\":\"\",\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-17 00:57:13', '2016-02-17 00:57:13', '9977e66c-2cde-4dd3-8fa4-1bde63481201'),
 ('3682', '862', '3', '1', 'en_us', '6', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Choose a Suitable Location\",\"slug\":\"find-a-location\",\"postDate\":1453930440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"912\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h3>Some Factors to Consider<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol><li>What kind of location best suites your target customers (who walks by and who comes to visit the neighborhood)?&nbsp;<\\/li><li>How much space do you need?<\\/li><li>What kind of space will you need? Will you need special needs around&nbsp;plumbing,&nbsp;power, kitchens,&nbsp;etc.&nbsp;<\\/li><li>What are the lease terms?<\\/li><li>What can you afford to pay?<\\/li><li>How much parking do you need?<\\/li><\\/ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We recommend that you have a strong&nbsp;understanding of&nbsp;the business, zoning\\/planning, and building permitting needs of your location before you sign your lease.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>There are several resources to help you find a business location in Oakland, including city staff, commercial brokers, website listings, and shopping district leaders.&nbsp;The City of Oakland Business Assistance Center can provide market analysis on neighborhood profiles, demographic reports, and more.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1702\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"\",\"linkTitle\":\"Request Assistance from the BAC\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/oaklandbusinesscenter.com\\/request.html\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-17 01:03:06', '2016-02-17 01:03:07', '28e91e50-775a-4779-93f1-870bed35aa94'),
 ('3692', '1712', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Check Zoning Regulations for Your Property\",\"slug\":\"check-zoning-regulations-for-your-property\",\"postDate\":1455146400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"912\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Once you have a couple of location options, you should check&nbsp;the planning map and zoning code&nbsp;to see if your location outright permitted, conditionally permitted or not permitted.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>This step can be complicated depending on the type of business. Unless you are familiar with planning and zoning regulations, we recommend you talk with a planner at the City of&nbsp;Oakland.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1722\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"Talk to a Planner\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Permit Center<br><\\/strong>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 2114<br>Oakland, CA 94612<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}},\"1732\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Online Resource\",\"linkTitle\":\"See the Zoning Map\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/mapgis.oaklandnet.com\\/planmap\\/\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}},\"1742\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Online Resource\",\"linkTitle\":\"Read the Municipal Planning Code\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/report\\/oak053289.pdf\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-17 01:04:31', '2016-02-17 01:04:31', 'ea1cb413-c7e8-45a9-81a5-6b53b981ab51'),
 ('3702', '1712', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Check Zoning Regulations for Your Property\",\"slug\":\"check-zoning-regulations-for-your-property\",\"postDate\":1455146400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"912\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Once you have a couple of location options, you should check&nbsp;the planning map and zoning code&nbsp;to see if your location outright permitted, conditionally permitted or not permitted.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>This step can be complicated depending on the type of business. Unless you are familiar with planning and zoning regulations, we recommend you talk with a planner at the City of&nbsp;Oakland.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1722\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"Talk to a Planner\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Permit Center<br><\\/strong>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 2114<br>Oakland, CA 94612<br>1&nbsp;(510) 238-3911<br><br><\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}},\"1732\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Online Resource\",\"linkTitle\":\"See the Zoning Map\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/mapgis.oaklandnet.com\\/planmap\\/\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}},\"1742\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Online Resource\",\"linkTitle\":\"Read the Municipal Planning Code\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/report\\/oak053289.pdf\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-17 01:08:36', '2016-02-17 01:08:36', 'f779f76d-068c-403e-a68a-a6352873843d'),
 ('3712', '932', '3', '1', 'en_us', '5', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Check Your Location with Utility Companies\",\"slug\":\"start-your-utilities\",\"postDate\":1453933500,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"912\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h2>Local Utility&nbsp;Providers<\\/h2><ul><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.pge.com\\/\\\">PG&E<\\/a> (Electricity and Gas)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.ebmud.com\\/\\\">EBMUD<\\/a> (Water and Sewage)<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.acgov.org\\/aceh\\/\\\">Alameda Country Environmental Health<\\/a><\\/li><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.xfinity.com\\/\\\">Comcast<\\/a> (Internet)<\\/li><\\/ul><p> Make sure to contact your utility providers&nbsp;as soon as you find your location to get everything&nbsp;in order.&nbsp; Depending on the services you need, your building may require&nbsp;upgrades which take additional time and money.&nbsp;It is recommended that you get your requests in early.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1592\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"\",\"linkTitle\":\"Visit PG&E Online\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/pge.com\\/\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-17 01:21:57', '2016-02-17 01:21:57', 'fc5d18a0-d207-4d74-a499-12d11027db3c'),
 ('3722', '1012', '3', '1', 'en_us', '6', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Common Permit Types\",\"slug\":\"permits-by-common-business-types\",\"postDate\":1453936200,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"992\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>The following are standard permits required for common types of businesses. However, this is not a complete list for all types of businesses.&nbsp; Make sure to check CalGold website to get the permits needed for your type of business, as described at the bottom of this page.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>City of Oakland Requirements<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Building Permits<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Building permits are documents which are obtained through the Office of Planning and Building authorizing the start of construction or remodeling of a building in the City of Oakland. There are four types of permits which may be required:&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol><li>Building<\\/li><li>Electrical<\\/li><li>Plumbing<\\/li><li>Mechanical<\\/li><\\/ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.oaklandnet.com\\/government\\/ceda\\/revised\\/building_permits.html\\\">Get more details from Building Services<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Rent Adjustment<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you rent out one or more residential units, you may be subject to the City of Oakland\\u2019s Rent Program service fee of $30 per year per unit.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/cedaonline.oaklandnet.com\\/rentadjustmentsite\\/index.htm\\\">Get details here<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Excess Litter Fee<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you are operating one of the types of businesses below, you may be subject to the Excess Litter Fee.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Fast food restaurants\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Convenience markets\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Gasoline station markets\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Liquor stores&nbsp;<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.oaklandnet.com\\/documents\\/WEBPAGEELF92206.pdf\\\">Get more details in this PDF file<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Peddler\\/Solicitor Permit<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you intend to sell or solicit door-to-door, you must obtain a peddler permit.&nbsp; Obtain the permit application at:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Oakland Police Department<br>455 7th Street, Room 306<br>Oakland, 94607.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Bring the completed Peddler Permit to the Business Tax office.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Fire Department Permits<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you are starting a new business, or are expanding an existing business in Oakland which includes the operation, and\\/or storage and\\/or manufacturing of a wide variety of items, you are required to submit a permit application to the Fire Prevention Office. Your application will be reviewed, an inspection of your business will be conducted, and a determination will be made as to the issuance of the permit.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Important note: Business owners are advised to&nbsp;<\\/strong><strong>meet with the Oakland Fire Department early on<\\/strong>&nbsp;in your planning stage, as many permits are rejected annually due to wrong use code and other issues found during the inspection phase. Meeting with the Oakland Fire Department from the onset will save you time and money as you are starting or expanding your business. Don\'t assume that your business doesn\'t apply!<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.oaklandnet.com\\/fire\\/fpb\\/\\\">Get more details from the Fire Prevention Office<\\/a>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>County and State&nbsp;Requirements<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Fictitious Business Name<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You must register your business name with the Alameda County Clerk-Recorder\'s Office.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.acgov.org\\/auditor\\/clerk\\/filefbn1.htm\\\">More details from Alameda County Clerk-Recorder\'s Office<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Retail\\/Wholesale Sales<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you will be selling retail or wholesale items which require collection of state sales taxes, you need a Sellers Permit.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.boe.ca.gov\\/\\\">More details from California State Board of Equalization<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Food Establishments<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you will be serving and selling food, you must obtain a health permit before applying for your Business Tax Certificate.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.acgov.org\\/aceh\\/\\\">More details from Alameda County Environmental Health<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Alcoholic Beverage Sales<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If you intend to sell alcoholic beverages, you must have an Alcoholic Beverage License.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.abc.ca.gov\\/\\\">More details from California state Alcoholic Beverage Control<\\/a><\\/p><h3>Hazardous Waste<\\/h3><p>If your company intends to deal with hazardous waste&nbsp;(such as solvents, motor oil, paints, pesticides, fertilizers,&nbsp;aerosol, etc), you will need to apply for a hazardous waste permit with the County of Alameda.<\\/p><p>For more details, call&nbsp;Alameda County Environmental Health at 1&nbsp;(510) 567-6702 or visit their <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.acgov.org\\/aceh\\/\\\">website<\\/a>.<\\/p>\",\"312\":\"\",\"4\":\"Learn more about permits that are required by common business types\"}}', '2016-02-17 01:37:20', '2016-02-17 01:37:20', 'e75a0f72-99e8-46b5-81f7-461a8c8e4924'),
 ('3732', '872', '3', '1', 'en_us', '11', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Obtain a Zoning Clearance Permit\",\"slug\":\"obtain-a-zoning-permit\",\"postDate\":1453931700,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"922\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>If you plan to operate a business in Oakland (including a home office), you will need to obtain a zoning permit called a&nbsp;<strong>Zoning Clearance<\\/strong>. You do not need a&nbsp;<strong>Zoning Clearance<\\/strong>&nbsp;if your business is located outside of Oakland or if your business activity is a rental property operator. The Zoning Clearance is granted if your business is allowed in the proposed location. In some instances, ahead of obtaining a Zoning Clearance, a proposed business activity must also go through a special&nbsp;<strong>Conditional Use Permit&nbsp;<\\/strong>process to determine whether the activity will be allowed.&nbsp;<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Zoning Clearance is a one-time permit that is good as long as the nature of your business remains the same and in the same location. You will need this zoning permit before applying for your business tax certificate.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may obtain additional information about zoning permits and regulations via the&nbsp;<strong>Zoning Hotline<\\/strong>&nbsp;(telephone), the&nbsp;<strong>Online Zoning Request Form<\\/strong>&nbsp;or by visiting the&nbsp;<strong>Permit Counter. Zoning Clearances<\\/strong>&nbsp;and other zoning permit applications are available online, but must be submitted and paid for in person at the Permit Counter.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Businesses Located in the&nbsp;Port Area<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Any development or construction in the Port Area of Oakland (seaport, airport, or Oakland Airport Business Park)&nbsp;must be approved by the Port prior to start of work, and prior to submittal for a City of Oakland&nbsp;building permit.&nbsp;Submit a completed <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.portofoakland.com\\/pdf\\/opportunities\\/permit_application2016.pdf\\\">application<\\/a> and a project description to Joe Marsh, Port Permit Coordinator, 530 Water Street, Oakland, jmarsh@portoakland.com<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1522\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Download\",\"linkTitle\":\"Get the Zoning Clearance Form\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/agenda\\/oak040732.pdf\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"1542\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"Turning In Your Application In Person\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Permit Counter<\\/strong><br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Room 2114<br>Oakland, CA 94612<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"A zoning clearance permit is required if you plan to operate your business in Oakland\"}}', '2016-02-17 01:44:52', '2016-02-17 01:44:52', '3a93f443-d3e4-45b7-a232-44032cba5b0f'),
 ('3742', '1092', '3', '1', 'en_us', '5', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Submit for Plan Check Review\",\"slug\":\"check-your-building-plan\",\"postDate\":1454962860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"1062\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Once you have submitted all of your&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/Government\\/o\\/PBN\\/OurServices\\/permits\\/index.htm\\\">required documents and building permit fees<\\/a>, our Building Services engineers will review your plans for&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/Government\\/o\\/PBN\\/OurOrganization\\/BuildingServices\\/s\\/codes\\/index.htm\\\">compliance with applicable codes and regulations<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Plan check for new dwellings usually takes four to six weeks. However, plans with special engineering may take longer. Building Services will also submit your plans to the Fire Services agency for review. Fire review takes 1-10&nbsp;days.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When you apply for your&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/Government\\/o\\/PBN\\/OurServices\\/permits\\/index.htm\\\">Building Permit<\\/a>, Zoning staff will review the plans submitted to ensure that all conditions of approval are satisfied and that the plans are consistent with Zoning approval.&nbsp;If we return your plans to you for revision and resubmittal, plan check time will increase accordingly. For answers to your plan check questions, please call (510) 238-3891.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1582\":{\"type\":\"phoneNumber\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"phoneNumberTitle\":\"By Phone\",\"number\":\"1 (510) 238-3891\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"new1\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"In Person\",\"address\":\"<p>Permit Center<br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 2114<br>Oakland, CA 94612<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-17 01:47:55', '2016-02-17 01:47:55', 'f0b367fd-3952-43fd-a3fd-9dc096258e21'),
 ('3752', '1892', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Schedule an Inspection with the Police Department\",\"slug\":\"schedule-an-inspection-with-the-police-department\",\"postDate\":1455674250,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"1832\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>You will need to schedule inspections with the Oakland Police Department if your business:<\\/p><ul><li>involves&nbsp;cannabis, alcohol, or cabaret<\\/li><li>hosts&nbsp;special events such as&nbsp;concerts<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"312\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"phoneNumber\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"phoneNumberTitle\":\"By Phone\",\"number\":\"(510) 777-3333\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"In Person\",\"address\":\"<p>Oakland&nbsp;Police Department<br>455 7th Street<br>Oakland, CA&nbsp;94607<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-17 01:57:30', '2016-02-17 01:57:30', 'ce414000-6b77-460e-85ae-29c9483784fd'),
 ('3762', '982', '3', '1', 'en_us', '15', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Schedule Your Building Inspections\",\"slug\":\"get-your-business-inspections\",\"postDate\":1453935180,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"1832\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h3>Building Services Hours<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Hours: Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, Friday 8:00a.m.- 4:00p.m&nbsp;and&nbsp;Wednesday 9:30a.m. - 4:00p.m.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Building Services inspections include ADA compliance&nbsp;mechanical, electrical, and plumbing inspections.&nbsp;It is your responsibility to schedule all inspections and ensure your business stays up to date with all the latest regulations.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Inspections are required to insure that the construction is proceeding according to the approved plans and project conditions-of-approval, and that all current code standards are being met.<\\/p><p>An appointment must be made at least one working day in advance, and during busy construction months they may take several days to schedule.&nbsp;Periodic inspections must be scheduled until the project is completed and the City gives final approval.&nbsp;After the job has received a final inspection, the building permit will be kept on file in the Building Services Department as proof of the work completed.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>During the construction phase, inspections by City Inspectors are required prior to:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Placing concrete or grout;<\\/li><li>Covering electrical, plumbing, or mechanical work;<\\/li><li>Covering floor framing;<\\/li><li>Covering interior sides of wall framing;<\\/li><li>Taping gypsum wallboard;<\\/li><li>Applying stucco;<\\/li><li>Insulation;<\\/li><li>Shower Walls prior to tiling;<\\/li><li>Exterior & Interior shear nailing;<\\/li><li>Waterproof membrane at exterior balconies, stairs etc;<\\/li><li>Roof plywood nailing;<\\/li><li>Roof framing;<\\/li><li>Shafts;<\\/li><li>Fire protection<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br><strong>Inspections are also required prior to connecting to, or the hook-up of:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Gas lines;<\\/li><li>Electrical service; and\\/or<\\/li><li>Water and sewer services.<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1762\":{\"type\":\"phoneNumber\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"phoneNumberTitle\":\"By Phone\",\"number\":\"1 (510) 238-3444 \",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"1772\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"In Person\",\"address\":\"<p>250 Frank Ogawa Plaza, 2nd Floor<br>Oakland, CA 94612<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-17 02:00:42', '2016-02-17 02:00:42', '6ca971c7-1153-4b79-8e31-528f8225beba'),
 ('3772', '882', '3', '442', 'en_us', '10', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Get Help Creating a Business Plan\",\"slug\":\"before-you-start\",\"postDate\":1453932720,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"742\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Before you get your license, find a location, or buy supplies or stock, it\'s important&nbsp;to plan out your business to&nbsp;project how much you will need and how much you will make over the next few years.&nbsp;This can prevent you from making big mistakes, going into credit card debt and&nbsp;other difficult situations. &nbsp;<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Templates of Business Plans:<\\/strong><br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.score.org\\/resources\\/business-planning-financial-statements-template-gallery\\\">SCORE<\\/a><\\/li><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.sbdcnet.org\\/small-business-information-center\\/business-plans\\\">SBDC<\\/a>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<em>organized by type of&nbsp;business<\\/em><\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.sba.gov\\/writing-business-plan\\\">SBA<\\/a><\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Local Business Plan Classes and Advisors:&nbsp;<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/acsbdc.org\\/\\\">Alameda County SBDC<\\/a><\\/li><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.eastbayscore.org\\/\\\">SCORE&nbsp;East Bay Chapter<\\/a><\\/li><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/anewamerica.org\\/index.php\\/program-highlight\\/160-announcing-new-business-development-classes-in-the-east-south-bay\\\">AnewAmerica<\\/a>&nbsp;<em>- focused on&nbsp;immigrant and minority entrepreneurs<\\/em><\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<hr>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>While working on your Business Plan, the City of Oakland\'s&nbsp;business development staff can help you learn more about your potential market.&nbsp;To request assistance on market analysis from the City staff, please&nbsp;complete a <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/oaklandbusinesscenter.com\\/request.html\\\">BAC Assistance Request form<\\/a> to learn more about:<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Neighborhood profiles<\\/li><li>Demographic reports<\\/li><li>Industry sector reports<\\/li><li>Traffic counts<\\/li><li>Sales tax trends<\\/li><li>Local taxes and costs<\\/li><li>Labor force information<\\/li><li>Major employer information<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"312\":\"\",\"4\":\"Templates, classes, and advisors for creating a business plan\"}}', '2016-02-18 22:16:13', '2016-02-18 22:16:13', 'e8259cb2-e3e3-450c-9550-dcddfbf2d9e7'),
 ('3782', '1922', '3', '442', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"442\",\"title\":\"Create a Business Plan and Get Financing\",\"slug\":\"create-a-business-plan-and-get-financing\",\"postDate\":1455833859,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"732\",\"fields\":{\"4\":\"\",\"282\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-18 22:17:40', '2016-02-18 22:17:40', 'd4ec4506-5e5a-4ce4-9fcd-869970180948'),
 ('3792', '1932', '3', '442', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"442\",\"title\":\"Get Financing for Your Business\",\"slug\":\"get-financing-for-your-business\",\"postDate\":1455835260,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>If you need money to start or grow your business, it is important to think about what type of financing best fits your business and aligns with your values. Different financing options include:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol><li>Loans from Community&nbsp;Organizations & Institutions<\\/li><li>Loans from Community Banks<\\/li><li>0% Loans from Peer-to-Peer Platforms<\\/li><li>Crowdfunding \\u2013 Reward\\/Donation-Based<\\/li><li>Crowdfunding \\u2013 Investment-Based<\\/li><li>Angel Investors<\\/li><li>Impact Investment Funds<\\/li><\\/ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Popular Oakland Financing Programs<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Oakland Business Development Center (OBDC)<\\/strong><br><em>Small business&nbsp;loans ranging from&nbsp;$10,000 to&nbsp;$25,000<br><\\/em>825 Washington St.,&nbsp;Ste. 200<br>Oakland, CA 94607<br>(510) 830-3275<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Kiva Zip<\\/strong><br><em>Peer to Peer donations for loans up to $25,000<br><\\/em>875 Howard St.<br>San Francisco, CA 94103<br>(713) 924-8170<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Small Business Loans\",\"linkTitle\":\"OBDC Website\",\"linkUrl\":\"www.obdc.com\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Peer to Peer Donations\",\"linkTitle\":\"Kiva Zip Website\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www.kivazip.org\\/\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Additional Financing Programs\",\"linkTitle\":\"SBA Good Local Money Guide\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/cdn.localon.com\\/upload-4722960365254482686.pdf\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-18 22:41:34', '2016-02-18 22:41:34', '0ac2d70a-4d4a-4870-9293-ad46f585125a'),
 ('3802', '1932', '3', '442', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"442\",\"title\":\"Get Financing for Your Business\",\"slug\":\"get-financing-for-your-business\",\"postDate\":1455835260,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"1922\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>If you need money to start or grow your business, it is important to think about what type of financing best fits your business and aligns with your values. Different financing options include:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol><li>Loans from Community&nbsp;Organizations & Institutions<\\/li><li>Loans from Community Banks<\\/li><li>0% Loans from Peer-to-Peer Platforms<\\/li><li>Crowdfunding \\u2013 Reward\\/Donation-Based<\\/li><li>Crowdfunding \\u2013 Investment-Based<\\/li><li>Angel Investors<\\/li><li>Impact Investment Funds<\\/li><\\/ol><p>For more information and programs within these&nbsp;financing options, please refer to the Small Business Association\'s (SBA) <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/cdn.localon.com\\/upload-4722960365254482686.pdf\\\">Good Local Money Guide<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Popular Oakland Financing Programs<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Oakland Business Development Center (OBDC)<\\/strong><br><em>Small business&nbsp;loans ranging from&nbsp;$10,000 to&nbsp;$25,000<br><\\/em>825 Washington St.,&nbsp;Ste. 200<br>Oakland, CA 94607<br>(510) 830-3275<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Kiva Zip<\\/strong><br><em>Peer to Peer donations for loans up to $25,000<br><\\/em>875 Howard St.<br>San Francisco, CA 94103<br>(713) 924-8170<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1942\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Small Business Loans\",\"linkTitle\":\"OBDC Website\",\"linkUrl\":\"www.obdc.com\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"1952\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Peer to Peer Donations\",\"linkTitle\":\"Kiva Zip Website\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www.kivazip.org\\/\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"1962\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Additional Financing Programs\",\"linkTitle\":\"SBA Good Local Money Guide\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/cdn.localon.com\\/upload-4722960365254482686.pdf\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-02-18 22:45:00', '2016-02-18 22:45:00', '3d9bd471-90e9-41af-a2b2-ddaf195cd226'),
 ('3812', '872', '3', '1', 'en_us', '12', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Obtain a Zoning Clearance Permit\",\"slug\":\"obtain-a-zoning-permit\",\"postDate\":1453931700,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"922\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>If you plan to operate a business in Oakland (including a home office), you will need to obtain a zoning permit called a&nbsp;<strong>Zoning Clearance<\\/strong>. You do not need a&nbsp;<strong>Zoning Clearance<\\/strong>&nbsp;if your business is located outside of Oakland or if your business activity is a rental property operator. The Zoning Clearance is granted if your business is allowed in the proposed location. In some instances, ahead of obtaining a Zoning Clearance, a proposed business activity must also go through a special&nbsp;<strong>Conditional Use Permit&nbsp;<\\/strong>process to determine whether the activity will be allowed.&nbsp;<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Zoning Clearance is a one-time permit that is good as long as the nature of your business remains the same and in the same location. You will need this zoning permit before applying for your business tax certificate.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may obtain additional information about zoning permits and regulations via the&nbsp;<strong>Zoning Hotline<\\/strong>&nbsp;(telephone), the&nbsp;<strong>Online Zoning Request Form<\\/strong>&nbsp;or by visiting the&nbsp;<strong>Permit Counter. Zoning Clearances<\\/strong>&nbsp;and other zoning permit applications are available online, but must be submitted and paid for in person at the Permit Counter.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Businesses Located in the&nbsp;Port Area<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Any development or construction in the Port Area of Oakland (seaport, airport, or Oakland Airport Business Park)&nbsp;must be approved by the Port prior to start of work, and prior to submittal for a City of Oakland&nbsp;building permit.&nbsp;Submit a completed <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.portofoakland.com\\/pdf\\/opportunities\\/permit_application2016.pdf\\\">application<\\/a> and a project description to Joe Marsh, Port Permit Coordinator, 530 Water Street, Oakland, jmarsh@portoakland.com<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Online Zoning Application\",\"linkTitle\":\"Apply Online\",\"linkUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/aca.accela.com\\/oakland\\/default.aspx\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"1522\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Download\",\"linkTitle\":\"Get the Zoning Clearance Form\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/agenda\\/oak040732.pdf\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}},\"1542\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"Turning In Your Application In Person\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Permit Counter<\\/strong><br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Room 2114<br>Oakland, CA 94612<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"A zoning clearance permit is required if you plan to operate your business in Oakland\"}}', '2016-02-22 18:17:31', '2016-02-22 18:17:31', '74ada088-1279-4741-98d7-247382c743bb'),
 ('3822', '872', '3', '1', 'en_us', '13', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Obtain a Zoning Clearance Permit\",\"slug\":\"obtain-a-zoning-permit\",\"postDate\":1453931700,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"922\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>If you plan to operate a business in Oakland (including a home office), you will need to obtain a zoning permit called a&nbsp;<strong>Zoning Clearance<\\/strong>. You do not need a&nbsp;<strong>Zoning Clearance<\\/strong>&nbsp;if your business is located outside of Oakland or if your business activity is a rental property operator. The Zoning Clearance is granted if your business is allowed in the proposed location. In some instances, ahead of obtaining a Zoning Clearance, a proposed business activity must also go through a special&nbsp;<strong>Conditional Use Permit&nbsp;<\\/strong>process to determine whether the activity will be allowed.&nbsp;<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Zoning Clearance is a one-time permit that is good as long as the nature of your business remains the same and in the same location. You will need this zoning permit before applying for your business tax certificate.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may obtain additional information about zoning permits and regulations via the&nbsp;<strong>Zoning Hotline<\\/strong>&nbsp;(telephone), the&nbsp;<strong>Online Zoning Request Form<\\/strong>&nbsp;or by visiting the&nbsp;<strong>Permit Counter. Zoning Clearances<\\/strong>&nbsp;and other zoning permit applications are available online, but must be submitted and paid for in person at the Permit Counter.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Businesses Located in the&nbsp;Port Area<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Any development or construction in the Port Area of Oakland (seaport, airport, or Oakland Airport Business Park)&nbsp;must be approved by the Port prior to start of work, and prior to submittal for a City of Oakland&nbsp;building permit.&nbsp;Submit a completed <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.portofoakland.com\\/pdf\\/opportunities\\/permit_application2016.pdf\\\">application<\\/a> and a project description to Joe Marsh, Port Permit Coordinator, 530 Water Street, Oakland, jmarsh@portoakland.com<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"1972\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Online Zoning Application\",\"linkTitle\":\"Apply for Zoning Clearance Online\",\"linkUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/aca.accela.com\\/oakland\\/default.aspx\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"1522\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Download\",\"linkTitle\":\"Get the Zoning Clearance Form\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/agenda\\/oak040732.pdf\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}},\"1542\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"Turning In Your Application In Person\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Permit Counter<\\/strong><br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Room 2114<br>Oakland, CA 94612<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"A zoning clearance permit is required if you plan to operate your business in Oakland\"}}', '2016-02-22 18:18:58', '2016-02-22 18:18:58', 'd3b52573-67ca-43d8-95f2-490c65547bd3'),
