rts on the first of the month after submission of your paperwork.<\\/li><li>You can change your plan during open enrollment during the fall.<\\/li><li>Any changes you make become effective in January of the following year.<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Medical Coverage<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You can choose a medical plan through CalPERS (California Public Employees Retirement Systems) Health Benefit Services.<br>The City pays the full monthly premium for some plans. For other plans, the employee pays premiums with after-tax dollars.<br>For more information on medical plans, visit the CalPERS website.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Dental Plans<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>All full time employees except fire and police can choose from two dental plans for themselves and their eligible dependents. The HMO dental plan includes no deductibles when visiting an authorized dentist. This plan is administered by DeltaCare.<br>The PPO plan covers a percentage of costs but gives members more flexibility. This plan is administered by Delta Dental. <br>Police and fire personnel have dental coverage through their respective unions.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Vision Care<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>All full time employees except fire and police have vision coverage for themselves and their eligible dependents. This plan is administered by Vision Service Plan.<br>Police and fire personnel do not have vision coverage.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Dependents<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Your dependents may be eligible for the same health care coverage that you enroll in.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Eligible dependents include:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Spouse<\\/li><li>Domestic partner<\\/li><li>Financially dependent children\\r\\n<ul><li>Medical benefits: Children under age 26<\\/li><\\/ul><ul><li>Dental and vision benefits: Children under age 18 or students age 19 - 25<\\/li><\\/ul><\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You need to provide documentation to add your dependents to your health plan.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Marriage certificate<\\/li><li>Certificate of domestic partnership<\\/li><li>Birth certificate<\\/li><li>Legal adoption or guardianship papers<\\/li><li>Affidavit for financially dependent children<\\/li><li>Proof of full-time enrollment in school<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Continuing Your Benefits<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Under COBRA, an employee and enrolled dependents may pay to continue medical, dental or vision coverage for a limited period of time if city-paid coverage ceases for reasons recognized under the law.<br>The cost for COBRA coverage equals the same premium the City pays monthly plus a 2% administrative fee.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Retirement<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>All employees of the City of Oakland have retirement benefits through the Public Employees\' Retirement System (CalPERS).<br>What happens to my CalPERS benefits if I leave the City?<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You may be able to take your retirement benefits with you. If you leave the City to work for another employer that also participates in CalPERS, your retirement benefit will continue. If your new employer does not participate in CalPERS, the funds may be rolled over into a qualified Individual Retirement Account (IRA). <br>Current and former City employees interested in learning more about their retirement benefits may contact CalPERS directly at (888)225-7377 or visit the CalPERS website at www.calpers.ca.gov. They may also contact the City of Oakland\'s Retirement Office at (510)238-6479, weekdays from 8:30am - 5:00pm.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Deferred Compensation<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Deferred Compensation Plan is a voluntary retirement plan. You can increase your retirement savings and reduce your tax burden by contributing to this 457(b) plan.<br>You can contribute as little as $10 per pay period. The maximum contribution allowed is defined by Federal regulations for the calendar year. You can choose from several investment options. The City does not contribute to nor match employee contributions to this plan.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Life Insurance<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>All full time employees including fire and police personnel have life insurance benefits. In the event of an employee\'s death, the beneficiary will receive an amount equal to the employee\'s current annual salary rounded up to the nearest $1,000. For example, if the annual salary is $35,500, the life insurance benefit would be $36,000.<br>If the death is the result of an accident, the beneficiary may receive an additional benefit equal to the life insurance amount.<br>The City pays the full premium cost for coverage. There is no employee contribution. Dependents are not eligible for this benefit.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><br>Disability<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Most part-time and full-time employees excluding police and fire personnel who experience a non-work-related illness or injury can apply for State Disability Insurance (SDI). This insurance is provided through the State of California\'s Employment Development Department.<br>Employees who do not qualify for SDI are covered by a third party administrator for both short- and long-term disability. Benefits begin after a seven-day period and are determined by several eligibility factors.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><br>Medical Waivers<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Upon proof of other medical coverage, employees may choose to waive or cancel medical benefits for themselves and eligible dependents and receive cash instead.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><br>Flexible Spending Accounts<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The City of Oakland offers three flexible spending programs: Medical Care Assistance Program (MCAP), Dependent Care Assistance Program (DCAP), Transit Program. <br>You contribute to these programs to pay for qualifying expenses with pre-tax dollars. This reduces the amount of tax dollars you pay. The IRS regulates these programs. Please visit the third party administrator website for specific information about the plans at http:\\/\\/www.cbadministrators.com.<br>The Medical Care Assistance Program (MCAP) allows an employee to pay for medical, dental and vision care expenses with pre-tax dollars up to $2,500 each year. Estimate your annual out-of-pocket medical costs to decide how much to contribute. The City will withhold contributions from your paycheck every two weeks.<br>The Dependent Care Assistance Program (DCAP) allows an employee to pay for dependent care expenses with pre-tax dollars up to $5000 per household. Only necessary dependent care that allows you, or both you and your spouse together, to work is eligible. Estimate your annual dependent-care costs to decide how much to contribute. The City will withhold contributions from your paycheck every two weeks.<br>After you pay for eligible expenses, submit a claim to the third party administrator for reimbursement.<br>The Transit Program allows an employee to pay for mass transit and parking with pre-tax dollars. Estimate your monthly transportation costs to decide how much to contribute. You may have to pay an administrative fee for the program.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The third party administrator will mail you a monthly voucher or transit card. You may use vouchers or transit cards at locations that accept tickets and passes. For more information, visit CBA, the third party administrator\'s website at http:\\/\\/www.cbadministrators.com.<\\/p>\",\"312\":\"\",\"4\":\"Salary information, benefits and compensation for City employees\"}}', '2016-03-07 23:29:29', '2016-03-07 23:29:29', '7bf5abec-9088-40b8-b646-5e53aff3c097'),
