 ('5652', '3212', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Challenge a Rent Increase (Draft)\",\"slug\":\"challenge-a-rent-increase\",\"postDate\":1459371180,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"3082\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h3>Understanding Limits to Rent Increases<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Increases are limited to the CPI adjustment announced each year by the Residential Rent Adjustment Program unless the landlord can justify a higher amount. The law limits these to specific reasons for a higher rent increase.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Only one increase is allowed in a twelve month period. &nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/li><li>Generally, if tenants do not file a petition within 60 days of receiving a rent increase, they will lose their rights to challenge the increase.<\\/li><li>In most cases, there is no limit on increases when a tenant moves out and a new tenant moves in. Once the new tenant moves in, future increases are limited by the Rent Law.<\\/li><\\/ul><h3>Understand the Process of Challenging a Rent Increase<\\/h3><ol><li>File a Petition with the Rent Adjustment Board.<\\/li><li><strong>Optional:<\\/strong>&nbsp;Attend a mediation session with your landlord to see if you can reach an agreement.<\\/li><li>Schedule a hearing with the Rent Adjustment Board.<\\/li><li>Prepare evidence and witnesses for the hearing.<\\/li><li>Go to your hearing.<\\/li><\\/ol><p>The Hearing Officer will decide what to do about the increase based on their interpretation of the law. You and your landlord must obey the decision.<\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/form\\/dowd008122.pdf\\\">Read the Full Tenants Guide for Detailed Information<\\/a><\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"formLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"formLabel\":\"Download the Form\",\"formButtonText\":\"Tenant Petition Form\",\"formLink\":[\"3482\"],\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"File In Person or By Mail\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Rent Adjustment Program<br><\\/strong>P. O. Box 70243<br>Oakland, California 94612-0243<br>(510) 238-3721<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-04-07 22:54:51', '2016-04-07 22:54:51', '7cc92b3e-e5b3-42d7-b564-00f8d9acfdeb'),
 ('5662', '3212', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Challenge a Rent Increase (Draft)\",\"slug\":\"challenge-a-rent-increase\",\"postDate\":1459371180,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"3082\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h3>Understanding Legal&nbsp;Rent Increases<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Increases are limited to the CPI adjustment announced each year by the Residential Rent Adjustment Program unless the landlord can justify a higher amount. The law limits these to specific reasons for a higher rent increase.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Only one increase is allowed in a twelve month period.<\\/li><li>Rent can be increased&nbsp;if their are improvements or major repairs that add value to the property.<\\/li><li>Rent can be increased if there has been an increase in housing service costs such as taxes, insurance, utilities, water, garbage, mantainence, or managerial costs.<\\/li><li>In some cases, rent can be increased if there is an increase in debt service cost.<\\/li><li>Rent can be increased due to a previous deferred annual adjustment.<\\/li><li>Generally, if tenants do not file a petition within 60 days of receiving a rent increase, they will lose their rights to challenge the increase.<\\/li><li>In most cases, there is no limit on increases when a tenant moves out and a new tenant moves in. Once the new tenant moves in, future increases are limited by the Rent Law.<\\/li><\\/ul><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/form\\/dowd008123.pdf\\\">Read the Full Letter for Tenants About Rent Increase Policies<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Understand the Process of Challenging a Rent Increase<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol><li>File a Petition with the Rent Adjustment Board.<\\/li><li><strong>Optional:<\\/strong>&nbsp;Attend a mediation session with your landlord to see if you can reach an agreement.<\\/li><li>Schedule a hearing with the Rent Adjustment Board.<\\/li><li>Prepare evidence and witnesses for the hearing.<\\/li><li>Go to your hearing.<\\/li><\\/ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Hearing Officer will decide what to do about the increase based on their interpretation of the law. You and your landlord must obey the decision.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/form\\/dowd008122.pdf\\\">Read the Full Tenants Guide for Detailed Information<\\/a><\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"3492\":{\"type\":\"formLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"formLabel\":\"Download the Form\",\"formButtonText\":\"Tenant Petition Form\",\"formLink\":[\"3482\"],\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"3502\":{\"type\":\"physicalAddress\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"physicalAddressTitle\":\"File In Person or By Mail\",\"address\":\"<p><strong>Rent Adjustment Program<br><\\/strong>P. O. Box 70243<br>Oakland, California 94612-0243<br>(510) 238-3721<\\/p>\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-04-07 23:00:19', '2016-04-07 23:00:19', '087cb7bf-baaa-4d92-b270-8e0ef9d18716'),
 ('5672', '3222', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Challenge an Eviction (Draft)\",\"slug\":\"challenge-an-eviction\",\"postDate\":1459371180,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"3082\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>The City of Oakland does not handle renter\\/landlord disputes around evictions. If you need help disputing or challenging an eviction, explore some of the resources above.<\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Online\",\"linkTitle\":\"East Bay Community Law Center\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/ebclc.org\\/need-services\\/housing-services\\/\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-04-07 23:16:21', '2016-04-07 23:16:21', '12813755-7d35-461c-a7e3-deb7a4683487'),
 ('5682', '3642', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Becoming a Landlord (Draft)\",\"slug\":\"becoming-a-landlord\",\"postDate\":1460401054,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"3082\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Information coming soon.<\\/p>\",\"312\":\"\",\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-04-11 18:57:34', '2016-04-11 18:57:34', '31632abc-43d7-45bf-b39d-1d95bb23c68f'),
 ('5692', '3242', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Raise a Tenant\\u2019s Rent (Draft)\",\"slug\":\"raise-a-tenants-rent\",\"postDate\":1459371240,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"3082\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h2>Understand Rent Increase Limits<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Only one increase is allowed in a twelve month period&nbsp;limited to the Allowable Annual Rent Increase rate (CPI adjustment)&nbsp;.<\\/li><li>The landlord can justify a higher amount under the specific justifications listed at the bottom of this page.<\\/li><li>Generally, if tenants do not file a petition within 60 days of receiving a rent increase, they will lose their rights to challenge the increase.<\\/li><li>In most cases, there is no limit on increases when a tenant moves out and a new tenant moves in. Once the new tenant moves in, future increases are limited by the Rent Law.<\\/li><\\/ul><p>The Allowable Annual Rent Increase rate (CPI adjustment) is&nbsp;announced each year by the Residential Rent Adjustment Program.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Responding to a Tenant\'s&nbsp;Challenge to Rent Increase<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Tenants may <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/beta.oaklandca.gov\\/services\\/housing\\/rental-properties-renters-and-landlords\\/challenge-a-rent-increase#entry:3212\\\">challenge a rent increase<\\/a> if they believe it is more than the allowable amount. &nbsp;To challenge an increase, a tenant must file a petition within 60 days of service of the notice of rent increase (or within 60 days of first receiving a Rent Board form Notice to Tenants of the existence of the Rent Adjustment Program from the landlord, whichever is later).<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Once a petition is received, owners must file a response.<\\/li><li>Petitions and responses are considered filed when RECEIVED by the Rent Adjustment Program office.<\\/li><li>If tenants do not file a petition on time they waive their right to challenge a rent increase.<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Upon receipt of a petition to contest a rent increase, a Rent Adjustment Program staff member notifies the landlord of the tenant\'s complaint. Landlords are required to file a response form and provide documents supporting their claimed justification for any increase more than the annual general CPI adjustment allowed or the unit\'s exempt status from the Rent Adjustment Ordinance.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Justifications for Rent Increase Higher than the CPI Increase<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li><strong>Banking:&nbsp;<\\/strong>Saving rent increases that are not given in one year and imposing them in subsequent years.<\\/li><li><strong>Capital Improvements:<\\/strong>&nbsp;Seeking a rent increase based on improvements that materially add to the value of the property and appreciably prolong its useful life or adapt it to new building codes. These improvements must primarily benefit the tenant. Increases are divided among all units benefited by the improvement and are amortized (spread out) over five years. The increase expires at the end of 5 years.<\\/li><li><strong>Uninsured Repairs:&nbsp;<\\/strong>An increase for work performed to secure compliance with any state or local law to repair damage from fire, earthquake, or other casualty or natural disaster to the extent the repairs are not reimbursed by insurance. These increases are allocated and amortized like capital improvements.<\\/li><li><strong>Debt Service Costs:&nbsp;<\\/strong>An increase that allows an owner to collect rents sufficient to cover the combined housing service and debt service costs for a loan secured by the property to finance a purchase of the property or improvements in the property that directly benefits the tenants..<\\/li><li><strong>Increased Housing Service Costs:&nbsp;<\\/strong>An increase that compares two years of operating expenses and allows for an increase in situations where there has been an increase in those costs.<\\/li><li><strong>Constitutional Fair Rate of Return:<\\/strong>&nbsp;By law, owners must be allowed an increase that allows them to earn a fair rate of return on their investment.<\\/li><\\/ul><strong><br>NOTE:<\\/strong>&nbsp;An owner may take the CPI Increase OR any combination of individual adjustments, but not both.\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\",\"312\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"View Online\",\"linkTitle\":\"Allowable Annual Rent Increase (CPI Adjustment)\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/agenda\\/oak052826.pdf\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-04-11 19:14:36', '2016-04-11 19:14:36', '613f8914-ab1a-4ee9-a571-8532accc5af8'),
 ('5702', '3642', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Becoming a Landlord (Draft)\",\"slug\":\"becoming-a-landlord\",\"postDate\":1460401020,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"3082\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>There are two primary requirements to being a landlord in Oakland:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>1. Pay the&nbsp;Rent Program Service Fee<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Each year landlords are required to pay a fee, currently $30, for each rental unit they own.&nbsp;This fee is used to cover the costs of operating the City of Oakland\'s Rent Adjustment Program (formerly Residential Rent Arbitration) and implementation of the Just Cause for Eviction Ordinance (Measure EE).<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You do not have to pay this fee on a rental unit you live in, if it is your primary place of residence. Additionally, some units are exempt from the fee. See the exemptions list and information in the notice.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If the fee is paid on time, property owners are entitled to collect 1\\/2 of the fee ($15.00) from the tenant(s) of the rental unit for which the fee is paid. This amount is not rent and cannot be included when calculating a rent increase.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>2. Providing&nbsp;Required Notice To&nbsp;Tenants<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Owners must give tenants the Notice to Tenants of the Rent Adjustment&nbsp;Program,&nbsp;available from the Rent Adjustment Program office or at this website&nbsp;(Notice to Tenants) at the beginning of their tenancy, advising them of the existence and scope of the Rent Adjustment Program.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Owners must provide the same Notice to Tenants&nbsp;with each Notice of Change of&nbsp;Terms of Tenancy.&nbsp;A notice of rent increase that is given without the Notice to Tenants&nbsp;is invalid, if challenged.<\\/li><li>Failure to provide tenants with this notice can extend the time that tenants have to file petitions challenging rent increases.<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"312\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Download\",\"linkTitle\":\"Rent Program Service Fee Application\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/form\\/dowd008102.pdf\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Download\",\"linkTitle\":\"Notice to Tenants Of the Rent Adjustment Program\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/agenda\\/oak055125.pdf\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-04-11 19:51:24', '2016-04-11 19:51:24', 'c8575a30-a43f-461a-af12-e38555156540'),
 ('5712', '3642', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Becoming a Landlord (Draft)\",\"slug\":\"becoming-a-landlord\",\"postDate\":1460401020,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"3082\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>There are two primary requirements to being a landlord in Oakland:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>1. Pay the&nbsp;Rent Program Service Fee<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Each year landlords are required to pay a fee, currently $30, for each rental unit they own.&nbsp;This fee is used to cover the costs of operating the City of Oakland\'s Rent Adjustment Program (formerly Residential Rent Arbitration) and implementation of the Just Cause for Eviction Ordinance (Measure EE).<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You do not have to pay this fee on a rental unit you live in, if it is your primary place of residence. Additionally, some units are exempt from the fee. See the exemptions list and information in the notice.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>If the fee is paid on time, property owners are entitled to collect 1\\/2 of the fee ($15.00) from the tenant(s) of the rental unit for which the fee is paid. This amount is not rent and cannot be included when calculating a rent increase.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>2. Providing&nbsp;Required Notice To&nbsp;Tenants<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Owners must give tenants the Notice to Tenants of the Rent Adjustment&nbsp;Program,&nbsp;available from the Rent Adjustment Program office or at this website&nbsp;(Notice to Tenants) at the beginning of their tenancy, advising them of the existence and scope of the Rent Adjustment Program.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Owners must provide the same Notice to Tenants&nbsp;with each Notice of Change of&nbsp;Terms of Tenancy.&nbsp;A notice of rent increase that is given without the Notice to Tenants&nbsp;is invalid, if challenged.<\\/li><li>Failure to provide tenants with this notice can extend the time that tenants have to file petitions challenging rent increases.<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"312\":{\"3662\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Download\",\"linkTitle\":\"Rent Program Service Fee Application\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/form\\/dowd008102.pdf\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}},\"3672\":{\"type\":\"onlineLink\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"onlineTitle\":\"Download\",\"linkTitle\":\"Notice to Tenants\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/ceda\\/documents\\/agenda\\/oak055125.pdf\",\"primaryCallToAction\":\"1\"}}},\"4\":\"\"}}', '2016-04-11 19:51:35', '2016-04-11 19:51:35', 'bea5da50-0045-4723-abfb-d84a692d1352'),
