 ('192', 'field', '1', 'es', ' health care coverage all employees are eligible for health care coverage for themselves and their eligible dependents these plans may include health insurance medical coverage dental care and vision care summary of benefits healthdentalvision careworker s compdisability insurancelife insuranceretirementprofessional developmentunemployment insurancefull time employee not include fire and police xxxxxxxxxfire and police full time xxxxxxpart timexxxxxpart time senior aidesxxx what to know you are eligible to enroll on the date you are hired work with your department to enroll within 60 days if you wait more than 60 days to enroll you will face a penalty of a 90 day waiting period your coverage starts on the first of the month after submission of your paperwork you can change your plan during open enrollment during the fall any changes you make become effective in january of the following year medical coverage you can choose a medical plan through calpers california public employees retirement systems health benefit services the city pays the full monthly premium for some plans for other plans the employee pays premiums with after tax dollars for more information on medical plans visit the calpers website dental plans all full time employees except fire and police can choose from two dental plans for themselves and their eligible dependents the hmo dental plan includes no deductibles when visiting an authorized dentist this plan is administered by deltacare the ppo plan covers a percentage of costs but gives members more flexibility this plan is administered by delta dental police and fire personnel have dental coverage through their respective unions vision care all full time employees except fire and police have vision coverage for themselves and their eligible dependents this plan is administered by vision service plan police and fire personnel do not have vision coverage dependents your dependents may be eligible for the same health care coverage that you enroll in eligible dependents include spousedomestic partnerfinancially dependent children medical benefits children under age 26dental and vision benefits children under age 18 or students age 19 25 you need to provide documentation to add your dependents to your health plan marriage certificatecertificate of domestic partnershipbirth certificatelegal adoption or guardianship papersaffidavit for financially dependent childrenproof of full time enrollment in school continuing your benefits under cobra an employee and enrolled dependents may pay to continue medical dental or vision coverage for a limited period of time if city paid coverage ceases for reasons recognized under the law the cost for cobra coverage equals the same premium the city pays monthly plus a 2% administrative fee retirement all employees of the city of oakland have retirement benefits through the public employees retirement system calpers what happens to my calpers benefits if i leave the city you may be able to take your retirement benefits with you if you leave the city to work for another employer that also participates in calpers your retirement benefit will continue if your new employer does not participate in calpers the funds may be rolled over into a qualified individual retirement account ira current and former city employees interested in learning more about their retirement benefits may contact calpers directly at 888 225 7377 or visit the calpers website at www calpers ca gov they may also contact the city of oakland s retirement office at 510 238 6479 weekdays from 8 30am 5 00pm deferred compensation the deferred compensation plan is a voluntary retirement plan you can increase your retirement savings and reduce your tax burden by contributing to this 457 b plan you can contribute as little as $10 per pay period the maximum contribution allowed is defined by federal regulations for the calendar year you can choose from several investment options the city does not contribute to nor match employee contributions to this plan life insurance all full time employees including fire and police personnel have life insurance benefits in the event of an employee s death the beneficiary will receive an amount equal to the employee s current annual salary rounded up to the nearest $1 000 for example if the annual salary is $35 500 the life insurance benefit would be $36 000 if the death is the result of an accident the beneficiary may receive an additional benefit equal to the life insurance amount the city pays the full premium cost for coverage there is no employee contribution dependents are not eligible for this benefit disability most part time and full time employees excluding police and fire personnel who experience a non work related illness or injury can apply for state disability insurance sdi this insurance is provided through the state of california s employment development department employees who do not qualify for sdi are covered by a third party administrator for both short and long term disability benefits begin after a seven day period and are determined by several eligibility factors medical waivers upon proof of other medical coverage employees may choose to waive or cancel medical benefits for themselves and eligible dependents and receive cash instead flexible spending accounts the city of oakland offers three flexible spending programs medical care assistance program mcap dependent care assistance program dcap transit program you contribute to these programs to pay for qualifying expenses with pre tax dollars this reduces the amount of tax dollars you pay the irs regulates these programs please visit the third party administrator website for specific information about the plans at http www cbadministrators com the medical care assistance program mcap allows an employee to pay for medical dental and vision care expenses with pre tax dollars up to $2 500 each year estimate your annual out of pocket medical costs to decide how much to contribute the city will withhold contributions from your paycheck every two weeks the dependent care assistance program dcap allows an employee to pay for dependent care expenses with pre tax dollars up to $5000 per household only necessary dependent care that allows you or both you and your spouse together to work is eligible estimate your annual dependent care costs to decide how much to contribute the city will withhold contributions from your paycheck every two weeks after you pay for eligible expenses submit a claim to the third party administrator for reimbursement the transit program allows an employee to pay for mass transit and parking with pre tax dollars estimate your monthly transportation costs to decide how much to contribute you may have to pay an administrative fee for the program the third party administrator will mail you a monthly voucher or transit card you may use vouchers or transit cards at locations that accept tickets and passes for more information visit cba the third party administrator s website at http www cbadministrators com '),
