 ('202', 'field', '1', 'es', ' working for the city of oakland comes with many benefits job securitydiverse workforcebenefits including health care coverage for you and your family the city manages hiring differently than private companies most hiring is guided by the civil service board click here to learn more about the civil service board the information below is provided to guide you through the hiring process and answer frequently asked questions these guidelines describe the average process for hiring through the civil service board you may want to bookmark this page for reference your individual experience may differ from this process if you have questions please contact_______________________ stages of the hiring process search for open positionsapply for a positionapplication reviewcivil service examinationplacement on eligibility listdepartment interviewreceipt of job offer read more below for details about each step in the process 1 search for open positions there are four ways that you can search for current job openings with the city of oakland search online at apply online for current job openings visit city of oakland offices to see posted job announcements visit one of our one stop career centers throughout the city of oakland visit the city of oakland human resources department at 150 frank h ogawa plaza 2nd floor suite 2352 from 8 30 am to 5 00 pm monday friday if you don t see a job you want yet you can set up an alert to learn when a future job is posted complete a job interest card to receive this alert for the next 12 months you will receive an email when a new position matches the category you choose 2 apply for a position to apply to a specific position you must submit your application online at apply online for current job openings by the closing date the human resources department will email you to confirm receiving the application if you do not have access to a computer or internet access you can use a computer at any location of the city of oakland public library you can also use a work station of the city of oakland department of human resources management at 150 frank h ogawa plaza 2nd floor oakland ca 94612 from 9 am to 5 pm need help applying call neogov at 877 204 4442 for technical questions for all other questions call 510 238 3112 tty 238 3254 veterans you may be entitled to preference points which can help you get hired to receive your points you must have an honorable discharge submit form dd214 with your application on or before the final filing date for the position if you are a disabled veteran submit proof of your disability from the veteran s service with your application people with criminal convictions you can still apply to a job with the city of oakland each application will be given individual consideration based on job relatedness all records of conviction s will be reviewed this review may result in a request for additional information or termination if needed 3 application review once your application is submitted it will be reviewed in two stages review of minimum qualifications the human resources department will check that your experiences fits the qualifications listed in the job posting if your application satisfies the criteria it will move to the next stage review of supplemental questions depending on the criteria of the job you applied to you may be required to complete supplemental questions you must complete these questions if the job announcement says that the questions are required if these required questions are not answered your application will not be considered if the questions are optional it is best to answer the questions as completely as possible these responses may help your application move to the next stage of the hiring process 4 civil service examination examinations may include any combination of the following activities application reviewsreview for minimum qualificationssupplemental questionnairemultiple choice true false written testproblem exerci